<title>FRANCE: Alcatel seeks shared Thomson management.</title>
<headline>Alcatel seeks shared Thomson management.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1996-09-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>French company Alcatel Alsthom said on Thursday it hoped to share management of Thomson Multimedia if its bid to take over Thomson SA succeeds,</p>
<p>&quot;We would like to share management&quot; of this company, Alcatel chairman Serge Tchuruk told a news conference.  </p>
<p>Thomson Multimedia is the loss-making electronics consumer goods arm of Thomson SA which is being privatised.</p>
<p>Engineering giant Alcatel made an offer in July for Thomson.</p>
<p>Diversified conglomerate Lagardere has submitted a rival bid. -- Paris Newsroom +33 1 4221 5452</p>
